You show me yours.

349
00:25:09,255 --> 00:25:12,491
You don't have one?
Give it to me.

350
00:25:16,134 --> 00:25:17,902
Uncle, don't you have one?

351
00:25:21,482 --> 00:25:24,589
Have faith. I'll make a good one.
-I know.

352
00:25:28,844 --> 00:25:30,204
I'll give you a good one.

353
00:25:31,277 --> 00:25:33,722
Let's go.
-Let's go, boss.

354
00:25:50,205 --> 00:25:51,595
(Sighs)

355
00:25:54,674 --> 00:25:55,567
(Horn blares)

356
00:25:57,374 --> 00:26:05,761
(Indistinct chatter)

357
00:26:06,318 --> 00:26:10,372
I've read that cold drinks
are unhealthy.

358
00:26:10,507 --> 00:26:12,349
Everything is harmful
if you do it excess.

359
00:26:12,431 --> 00:26:15,199
I do everything in excess.

360
00:26:15,438 --> 00:26:18,186
Do you know when I am thirsty...

361
00:26:18,501 --> 00:26:20,818
...I drink cold drink instead of water?

362
00:26:21,215 --> 00:26:23,020
It is a very bad habit.

363
00:26:23,078 --> 00:26:24,673
I need an approval for
the school building.

364
00:26:24,875 --> 00:26:27,031
I have given you the approval.
Look at this.

365
00:26:27,872 --> 00:26:29,225
Look at this. The file is ready.

366
00:26:34,170 --> 00:26:35,106
Thank you, sir.

367
00:26:35,226 --> 00:26:38,145
Shall I tell you the truth?
I failed in eighth grade.

368
00:26:38,843 --> 00:26:42,464
But by Lord's blessings,
I am the education minister.

369
00:26:42,694 --> 00:26:44,401
But I have something lacking.

370
00:26:45,210 --> 00:26:49,021
A lacking that keeps pinching me within.

371
00:26:49,645 --> 00:26:51,848
Do you know what it is?
I am an illiterate.

372
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:54,425
I am uneducated... but I wish that...

373
00:26:54,795 --> 00:26:59,061
...the children of our state should study
well and become IAS and IPS officers.

374
00:26:59,516 --> 00:27:02,759
They should serve the society
like you are doing. Am I right?

375
00:27:02,940 --> 00:27:06,183
Look, you've already
taken a step towards it.

376
00:27:07,184 --> 00:27:08,737
Master, I've bought chocolates.

377
00:27:08,896 --> 00:27:10,790
Distribute it to the children.
-Give him.

378
00:27:12,973 --> 00:27:15,423
Headmaster, they were writing on
the wall with a charcoal.

379
00:27:15,450 --> 00:27:17,289
I caught them red-handed
and brought them here.

380
00:27:17,322 --> 00:27:20,561
Okay, you go... I will handle them.
You come here. Come here.

381
00:27:21,228 --> 00:27:23,542
What were you doing, idiots?
What were you doing?

382
00:27:23,599 --> 00:27:26,828
Will you write with charcoal on the wall?
You've become mischievous.

383
00:27:26,866 --> 00:27:29,993
(Wailing)
-Will you write with charcoal on the wall?

384
00:27:30,037 --> 00:27:33,133
Will you do so much mischief?
Fools, will you do it again? -Master...

385
00:27:33,579 --> 00:27:35,356
It is wrong to punish
children like this.

386
00:27:35,719 --> 00:27:39,437
Ms. Neha, you tell me... he was
writing on the wall with charcoal.

387
00:27:39,844 --> 00:27:41,926
Is it a good thing to write on the walls
with charcoal?

388
00:27:42,067 --> 00:27:43,527
No, you tell me.

389
00:27:43,560 --> 00:27:46,979
Ms. Neha, these two guys should be
rusticated from the school. -Why?

390
00:27:47,559 --> 00:27:49,475
Ms. Neha, those three criminals...

391
00:27:49,722 --> 00:27:52,525
...he is Avdesh's brother
and he is Gorak's brother.

392
00:27:53,636 --> 00:27:56,447
Do you want them to become criminals like
them after being rusticated from school?

393
00:27:59,296 --> 00:28:02,902
Master, minister has given approval
for the school building.

394
00:28:03,104 --> 00:28:04,889
This is good news. Wow.

395
00:28:04,957 --> 00:28:09,066
We'll do the paperwork with
the contractor that you've approved.

396
00:28:09,362 --> 00:28:11,016
I'll call Lakhan today.

397
00:28:11,669 --> 00:28:15,780
Lakhan?
But last time you said it was Paras.

398
00:28:15,909 --> 00:28:17,950
Paras was murdered.
-Murdered?

399
00:28:18,917 --> 00:28:22,660
Yes, those three guys killed him.
Their brothers.

400
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,824
What is your name?

401
00:28:31,359 --> 00:28:33,419
Mahesh.
-Manikant.

402
00:28:34,940 --> 00:28:36,880
Do they three meet you?

403
00:28:37,574 --> 00:28:40,866
They meet us sometimes.
They are going to Patna today.

404
00:28:42,367 --> 00:28:45,213
Why Patna?
-To look for Poonam.

405
00:28:47,056 --> 00:28:50,997
Who is Poonam?
-Avdesh's bride.

406
00:28:52,023 --> 00:28:55,181
(Emotional music)

407
00:29:09,483 --> 00:29:11,043
Are you Avdesh's mother?

408
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:17,537
Greetings. My name is Neha.

409
00:29:19,047 --> 00:29:21,547
I want to talk to you about Avdesh.

410
00:29:27,056 --> 00:29:28,849
You know that police is
looking for them, don't you?

411
00:29:31,208 --> 00:29:34,451
If they nab them,
they'll thrash them brutally.

412
00:29:34,745 --> 00:29:36,716
They'll send them to jail forever.

413
00:29:37,701 --> 00:29:39,090
I've heard lot of threats till now.

414
00:29:39,948 --> 00:29:42,166
Your threats make no difference
to my son.

415
00:29:45,298 --> 00:29:48,259
(Bird chirping)

416
00:29:48,991 --> 00:29:52,002
Believe me,
I'm not here to threaten you.

417
00:29:53,084 --> 00:29:54,743
I want to save those children.

418
00:29:55,574 --> 00:29:58,228
If possible,
I want to give them a good life.

419
00:29:59,283 --> 00:30:02,711
Don't you wish your son to get
educated and become a good man?

420
00:30:07,191 --> 00:30:08,290
(Bird chirping)

421
00:30:12,960 --> 00:30:15,069
(Bird chirping)

422
00:30:23,164 --> 00:30:23,845
Sit here.

423
00:30:27,362 --> 00:30:31,277
(Indistinct chatter)

424
00:30:50,898 --> 00:30:55,862
(Bird chirping)

425
00:31:06,998 --> 00:31:13,877
Five months ago, Avdesh ran away
from home after fighting with me.

426
00:31:17,742 --> 00:31:19,165
He never returned home.

427
00:31:24,221 --> 00:31:28,126
Mahesh told me that
he meets him sometimes.

428
00:31:38,794 --> 00:31:40,751
We didn't beget nasty children.

429
00:31:42,307 --> 00:31:43,271
They have become goons.

430
00:31:44,786 --> 00:31:45,983
(Sniffles)

431
00:31:54,423 --> 00:31:55,773
Everything was alright.

432
00:31:57,768 --> 00:32:00,972
It was during Avdesh's wedding.

433
00:32:03,990 --> 00:32:13,022
"In tender age, she got married."

434
00:32:14,090 --> 00:32:19,180
"I was innocent and beloved was naive."

435
00:32:21,191 --> 00:32:32,896
"What trouble I've landed into?
He doesn't understand anything."

436
00:32:33,363 --> 00:32:42,630
"Beloved is very mischievous,
what do I do?"

